Abstract: Permits the court to obtain and consider any and all past criminal history of
parties in a temporary restraining order proceeding.
Present law permits the court to issue a temporary restraining order to protect from abuse in
an ex-parte proceeding for good cause shown, and also authorizes the use of past history of
abuse or threats to determine the existence of an immediate and present danger of abuse.
Proposed law retains present law and authorizes the court, on its own motion, to obtain and
consider any and all past criminal history of the parties in a temporary restraining order
proceeding.
