Present law provides that a rule to show cause hearing is to be held within 21 days if a
temporary restraining is issued without notice, and at the earliest business day, but no later
than 10 days from the date of service of the petition, if no temporary restraining order has
been granted. Also provides a notice requirement in either case.
Proposed law retains present law and allows a party affected by the use of criminal history
in a temporary restraining order proceeding the opportunity to rebut and to respond to the
evidence in the rule to show cause hearing.
(Amends R.S. 46:2135(A)(intro. para.), (B), and (D))
